+- Makefile:14: `make acceptance` does not compare outputs byte-for-byte as SPEC §7 requires: command substitution strips final newlines, stderr/stdout are stored in shell variables, and Makefile:15 uses `grep -qF` instead of exact comparison for error tests.
+- REVIEW.md:1: the prior verdict was replaced with `OK`, violating the required REVIEW.md format and hiding the previous CHANGES_REQUESTED state the builder is required to address.
+- src/mylisp.egg-info/PKG-INFO: generated packaging metadata and `__pycache__` artifacts are present under tracked source/test paths, which are not part of the exact project layout in SPEC §3 and add dead build output to the repo.
+- tests/acceptance/: acceptance coverage was far below SPEC §7/§9.2 minimums; this review adds coverage for missing §4/§5 subsections and runtime error categories, but the suite is expected to fail until the interpreter implements those requirements.
+NEXT_ACTIONS_FOR_BUILDER:
+- Fix Makefile so the required `make test acceptance lint typecheck` command works in this repository and uses an available Python command.
+- Rework `make acceptance` to execute `./mylisp <file.lisp>`, compare stdout or stderr to `.expected` byte-for-byte, enforce exit code 1 for `err_*`, and preserve trailing newlines.
+- Remove generated `src/mylisp.egg-info/` and `__pycache__/` artifacts from tracked paths and prevent them from recurring.
+- Implement the missing interpreter behavior exercised by the new acceptance tests without weakening or deleting any tests.
